    outlook: "The next 6-12 months will be critical for Vedanta’s demerger. Regulatory approvals, IPO timelines, and debt restructuring will dictate the pace of the split. Investors should watch for:\n\n1. **IPO Roadshows** – Expected to begin in Q4 2026, these will gauge investor appetite for the demerged units.\n2. **Debt Markets** – Vedanta’s ability to refinance $2.5B in maturing debt will be a key litmus test.\n3. **Commodity Trends** – Aluminium and oil prices will directly impact valuations of the first three IPOs.\n4. **Promoter Actions** – Any stake sales or strategic partnerships could signal confidence (or caution) in the demerged entities.\n\nIf successful, Vedanta’s demerger could set a precedent for other Indian conglomerates, proving that breaking up isn’t just good for business—it’s essential for unlocking value.",
