    risks: ["Regulatory uncertainty could trigger a mass exodus of crypto businesses to more favorable jurisdictions.", "Investor confidence may decline, leading to reduced trading volumes and liquidity.", "Poland’s reputation as a tech and fintech hub could be damaged, deterring future investment."],
    opportunities: ["A revised bill could strike a better balance between regulation and innovation, attracting new players.", "Temporary KNF guidelines could provide short-term clarity, helping businesses comply with MiCA.", "Poland’s strong tech talent pool could still position it as a leader if regulatory issues are resolved."],
    outlook: "### What Happens Next?\nThe immediate focus will be on whether the Sejm can muster the votes to override Duda’s veto. If successful, the bill could become law within weeks—but that’s a big if. The ruling coalition would need support from opposition lawmakers, many of whom have been critical of the legislation.\n\nIf the veto stands, Poland’s crypto businesses will be forced to navigate MiCA without clear national guidance. The KNF may issue temporary rules, but these are unlikely to provide the same level of certainty as a full-fledged law. In the worst-case scenario, some firms could begin relocating as early as Q3 2026.\n\nThe next few weeks will be critical. With the MiCA deadline looming, Poland’s government will need to act fast—or risk watching its crypto sector slip away.",
    conclusion: "Poland’s third crypto bill veto in as many years is more than just a political setback—it’s a warning sign for an industry that’s running out of time. With the EU’s MiCA regulations set to take full effect in just two weeks, the country’s crypto businesses are facing an existential crisis. The question now isn’t whether Poland can afford to get this wrong, but whether it can afford to get it right too late. For an industry that thrives on speed and innovation, the clock is ticking, and the stakes couldn’t be higher.\n\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\n\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\n\nWhatsApp: \n\n*Default WhatsApp profile image placeholder*\n\nPublished by PulseTrends",
