    keyHighlights: ["Over 100 Ebola cases reported in Congo in the past month", "Children under 18 account for 60% of all reported cases", "The World Health Organization (WHO) has deployed emergency response teams to the affected areas", "Local health officials are struggling to contain the outbreak due to limited resources and lack of infrastructure", "The Congolese government has declared a state of emergency in response to the outbreak"],
    executiveSummary: "The latest Ebola outbreak in Congo has raised concerns among global health officials, with the number of reported cases exceeding 100 in the past month. The outbreak is disproportionately affecting children, with over 60% of all reported cases involving minors. The WHO has deployed emergency response teams to the affected areas, but local health officials are struggling to contain the outbreak due to limited resources and lack of infrastructure.",
    marketBackground: "The Ebola outbreak in Congo is the latest in a series of public health crises to affect the country in recent years. The outbreak has highlighted the need for improved healthcare infrastructure and emergency response systems in the region.",
    detailedAnalysis: "## Introduction\nThe Ebola outbreak in Congo has sparked widespread concern among global health officials, with the number of reported cases exceeding 100 in the past month. The outbreak is disproportionately affecting children, with over 60% of all reported cases involving minors.\n## The Response\nThe WHO has deployed emergency response teams to the affected areas, but local health officials are struggling to contain the outbreak due to limited resources and lack of infrastructure. The Congolese government has declared a state of emergency in response to the outbreak, but the situation remains dire.\n## What's at Stake\nThe Ebola outbreak in Congo has significant implications for global public health. If left unchecked, the outbreak could spread to other parts of the country, or even to neighboring countries. The international community must come together to support the response efforts and prevent further spread of the disease.\n\n---\n\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\n\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\n\nWhatsApp:\n\n*Default WhatsApp profile image placeholder*\n\nPublished by PulseTrends\n\n---",
    expertInsights: "According to Dr. Maria Van Kerkhove, a leading expert on Ebola, 'the current outbreak in Congo is a stark reminder of the need for improved healthcare infrastructure and emergency response systems in the region.' Dr. Van Kerkhove added that 'the international community must come together to support the response efforts and prevent further spread of the disease.'",
