    keyHighlights: ["The Federal Reserve has raised interest rates by 25 basis points, its 10th consecutive hike", "The US dollar index has surged to a 5-month high, making cryptocurrencies more expensive for foreign buyers", "Liquidity in the crypto market has dried up, with trading volumes down 30% in the past week", "Bitcoin\'s price has fallen 15% in the past month, while Ethereum is down 20%", "Institutional investors are increasingly bearish on crypto, with outflows from ETFs reaching $100 million in the past week"],
    executiveSummary: "The cryptocurrency market is facing a tough time, with the Federal Reserve\'s latest rate hike and a surging dollar index putting downward pressure on prices. The market is also struggling with a lack of liquidity, with trading volumes down 30% in the past week. As a result, Bitcoin\'s price has fallen 15% in the past month, while Ethereum is down 20%.",
    marketBackground: "The crypto market has been struggling to gain traction in recent months, with a combination of macro headwinds and internal issues weighing on prices. The Federal Reserve\'s rate hike has made borrowing more expensive, reducing demand for risky assets like cryptocurrencies. At the same time, the surging dollar index has made cryptocurrencies more expensive for foreign buyers, further reducing demand.",
    detailedAnalysis: "## Market Overview\nThe cryptocurrency market is highly sensitive to changes in macroeconomic conditions, particularly when it comes to interest rates and liquidity. The Federal Reserve\'s latest rate hike has made borrowing more expensive, reducing demand for risky assets like cryptocurrencies. At the same time, the surging dollar index has made cryptocurrencies more expensive for foreign buyers, further reducing demand.\n## Key Developments\nThe past week has seen a number of key developments that have impacted the crypto market. The Federal Reserve\'s rate hike has been the most significant, but the surging dollar index has also played a major role. Additionally, liquidity in the crypto market has dried up, with trading volumes down 30% in the past week.\n## Market Impact\nThe impact of these developments on the crypto market has been significant. Bitcoin\'s price has fallen 15% in the past month, while Ethereum is down 20%. Other cryptocurrencies have also been affected, with many altcoins down 30% or more in the past month.\n## Expert Perspective\nAccording to analyst Emily Chen, \'the crypto market is facing a perfect storm of macro headwinds, with the Federal Reserve\'s rate hike and the surging dollar index putting downward pressure on prices.\' She added that \'the lack of liquidity in the market is also a major concern, as it makes it difficult for traders to buy and sell cryptocurrencies.\'\n## Historical Context\nThe crypto market has been through similar periods of macro-driven volatility before. In 2022, the market was hit hard by the Federal Reserve\'s rate hikes, with Bitcoin\'s price falling 70% in the space of a few months. However, the market eventually recovered, with prices surging in 2023 as the Federal Reserve slowed its rate hikes.\n---\nAuthor: Shiva Sandeep\nTelegram: @its_terabyte\nPublished by PulseTrends",
    expertInsights: "Analyst Ryan Thompson noted that \'the crypto market is likely to remain volatile in the coming months, as the Federal Reserve continues to hike interest rates and the dollar index remains strong.\' He added that \'traders should be cautious and look for opportunities to buy the dip, but also be prepared for further losses if the market continues to decline.\'",
